text.section:
Prior to a hearing on the need for an emergency appointment of a limited guardian or limited conservator, a petition shall be filed which sets forth the following:
The name, age, and address of the respondent;
The danger alleged to be imminent;
The type of appointment and the protection and assistance requested;
The facts and reasons supporting the request;
The name, address, and qualifications of the proposed limited guardian or limited conservator, if any;
The name, address, and interest of the petitioner;
The names and addresses of the respondent's next of kin, if known;
The name and address of the individual or facility, if any, having custody of the respondent; and
The date of filing of the petition for determination of disability or partial disability.
